<name>Robert Anthony< /name><Pics>None</Pics>< review>
Well they're not the most honest, not the cheapest, def not the best quality, not the most convenient... really not the very best in any particular category, but WAIT- this is not a negative review- I love these guys because in each of those categories, they are CLOSE to the top. All things averaged out, these guys are the best in SD County for people like me. They are reliable AF. If you rely on cannabis as your primary daily medicine, not just a "party drug," then I reccomend you come here. Their bud is not super strong, but I don't want it that way. Personally I think the "pro's" are making it way too strong lately.

I think this is the bottom line- their COMBINATION of quality and price absolutely cannot be beat in San Diego County- at least not as far as I've discovered so far.

ONE big caveat- I do NOT love the way the owners have obviously been prioritizing good looking employees over knowledgeable employees- the whole "budtender" concept, with tipjars and hot girls SUCKS- like it's a trendy bar or something. It's not booze guys.<//review>

I love going to the Chico Meat locker. They are one of the best butcher's we have in town. They take food stamps which is a great help for some of the people who are low income based in town. They do deli sandwiches, but if you want it hot it wont be covered by food stamps. The staff inside is amazing and always friendly. Dont be afraid to ask questions, they are always willing to help.</Review>

< Review>
From the first email to adding one last song to the end of the night, Robert, Maria, Kenji and the whole Noor team were amazing. We visited the Sofia Ballroom probably about 20+ times and each time the team was so patient to answer every question Alex, our parents and myself had. And there were A LOT.

We needed a large enough venue for 200+ guests: check. It needed to be mostly inside since February is unpredictable, but since it‚Äôs California we wanted some outdoor aspect: check.

A large greenery accent wall, champagne tower and the most amazing bar: check check and check.

The Noor staff had to deal with my 2020 wedding for over a year and a half. Kenji was my site coordinator and I could not have asked for a better person to help make all my wedding dreams come true. Every email and voicemail were answered in less than 24 hours and always ended with please let me know if you have any more questions. Countless parts of our wedding were changed all the way to just days before and he always found a solution to ease my panic. Thankful is an understatement for how I feel about Kenji. Every detail and even some surprises were  were met with excitement. February 22,2020 was out favorite day.

Robert is a food and wine enthusiast. Everyone knows as long as your guests stomachs are satisfied and thirst is quenched, your wedding is off to an amazing start. To stay in ‚Äúbudget‚Äù we booked with one of Noor‚Äôs several promotions they offer throughout the year. Chicken has a bad rep in the wedding world. Both chicken options, herb roasted chicken with mash potatoes and vegetables and portobello mushroom chicken with fingerling potatoes and vegetables,  were not only served hot but were flavorful and large. Our vegetarian option was the portobello mushroom ravioli with vegetables and even the meat eaters wanted a piece of it.

As a gift from Noor, Alex and I enjoyed filet mignon, prawns, mash potatoes and vegetables. YUM!

4 super bartenders held down an open bar for 200+ adults, we had an adult only wedding, for 6 hours. After the countless food complements, the our guests were amazed how their drink order were memorized and never had to wait for their drinks. I am not lying when I say there were always 60+ people hovering the bar the whole time.

Onto the party outside. Music was playing and cigars were enjoyed while guest enjoyed fresh air without getting soaked in the rain. Noor also allows outsource food venders for late night snacks, so our guests enjoyed made to order tacos and chilaquiles.

We had the best vendors and most of them Noor never worked with. Each one of the vendors complimented Kenji on his diligence and organization.

My only complaint of the night is that 6 hours was not enough. 12 hours wouldn‚Äôt have been. Noor hosted a night of family, friends, and the best fiesta this East Coast West Coast - Irish/ Mexican couple could have ever dreamt of.< /Review>

{'time': 1601166025440, 'text': "Hi Danielle,\n\nCOVID-19 is our unfortunate new reality. Although our Contracts clearly state that Clients lose their deposit if they cancel their event, we modified our agreement to allow ALL of our Clients whose events were impacted by California's stay at home orders to reschedule their events up to one year from their original date without penalty and at the same price and minimums that they reserved their event.  Our Clients can also choose to cancel their event and apply 100% of their deposits as credit towards another event at NOOR up to 24 months from the date of cancellation or order meals from our extensive catering service, NOORtoGO.com, for a celebration at home.\n\nWe are also working with the City of Pasadena's Health Department to safely re-open for al fresco dining in our outdoor venue, NOOR | Terrace under re-opening guidelines for restaurants.\n\nWe are all in this together and understand that at any time and without notice, our governor, public health officials, and/or mayor may decide to temporarily restrict gatherings or modify the stay at home order.  All of our livelihoods have been affected; our employees, our clients, our vendors and management. The pandemic has had a profound financial impact on everyone, but together we will prevail and celebrate again.  If your event must be postponed due to state or local restrictions, CDC recommendations, or Public Health guidelines, our sales team will help you figure out which of our options will work best for you.  Please feel free to contact me directly to discuss further.\n\nThank you.\n\nRobert Shahnazarian, Jr.\nSr. VP of Sales & Marketing\ne: robert@noorevents.com"}< /response>

We had our wedding party here last month (in the Sofia Ballroom) and it was fantastic! The bridge offered the opportunity to have a very loud, fun, and exciting entrance; the food was delicious; and we both cannot say enough about Miranda! She did an amazing job as our coordinator- super responsive, positive attitude, great with brainstorming ideas... she genuinely wanted us to have the best day possible!

The pros: smoking area in outside balcony that is attached to the foyer (so people don‚Äôt have to go far to get some air), food was delicious and portions were generous, spacious bridal suite, old Hollywood vibe, parking lot is close enough where guests don‚Äôt have to walk too far in their heels and dresses, and, did I mention Miranda? She was the best part of Noor for us.

The cons are: upcharges for minutiae, guests have to pay for parking ($6) the signage in the lot is sparse, the directions to the parking garage and to the banquet hall are different which can cause confusion, and the room is dim. Also there wasn‚Äôt an option to take home leftovers and there was SO MUCH food leftover. Miranda was kind enough to grab food for me and the groom, though, which we really appreciated.</Review>

<Text>I plan dozens of events a year, from small business functions, to large charitable events, and even weddings. It's RARE to find a venue like Noor Ballroom. In my humble opinion, what makes Noor better than your average venue is not the absolutely delicious food, it's not the amazingly beautiful venue, it's not even the ridiculously reasonable prices. No, all those things are icing on the cake, but what makes this particular venue stand out in a sea of places with tasty food, ambience, and comparable prices is the SERVICE.

I threw a big charitable Halloween Ball at the Ella Ballroom last night for 200 guests. Robert Shahnazarian was a dream to work with from start to finish. He made the process so simple, from our first phone call, to the venue walk-though, to the menu planning, and all the way through leading up to the day of the event. He listened to my needs, worked within my budget, followed up promptly, gave me great insight and ideas to enhance our event, and he did everything effortlessly and efficiently. He knows exactly what he's doing, and that takes away a lot of the stress of planning a large event.

On the day of the event, the on-site manager did a great job seeing to our needs, the staff were professional and efficient, and they rolled with all of the punches (helped us with a stand for our step & repeat banner when our stand wasn't the right type, moved furniture around to accommodate the needs of our vendor sponsors, did a great job passing the appetizers and tending the bar, etc.) Robert even dropped in to say hello and make sure everything was running smoothly, and then sent me a follow-up email in the morning to ensure that I was happy with how everything came together.

I would recommend this venue without a shadow of a doubt. I will look to them for future venue needs, and will refer them to friends, clients, and family. They have my full stamp of approval. THANK YOU for helping to make my event a successful one!<//Text>< Pics>

<text>Paige, the event manager completely ruined my wedding night for me and my family. One example is how she disrespected my mom and aunt when we were running behind schedule and it was getting close to the end time of the event. I don't know how any of that was their fault and why she needed to be rude about it. She approached me as it was getting close to 1am and asked if I wanted to extend the time to 130am and I gave her the okay. The credit card we put on file months before no longer worked because it was lost and we replaced it with another, and with a million things to do before the wedding I forgot to replace the one I had on file with the new card. So as soon as it declined she approached my mom and in front of our guests tells her that the credit card declined, and to get her new card right away. My mom was so embarrassed in front of our guests as anyone would be, but clearly the only thing on Paige's mind was making sure she got the extra $500 for the half hour at that very moment. My mom kindly asked her if she could give her the new card after the wedding was over because her purse was in the Noor bridal suite which is further away from the venue. It would have been inconvenient for her to leave the venue to get her credit card especially with a half hour left. But Paige threw a tantrum, and my coordinator who also thought she was extremely rude that night, had to calm her down and asked her to wait until the wedding was over. This would have been the sensible thing to do than to bother the brides mother. My poor mom was really shocked by how she was treated.

If I could go back i would have chosen a different venue for my wedding. For what you end up paying, just pay a couple thousand more and have your wedding at the Hilton or somewhere nicer that actually values good customer service. < Review>
It‚Äôs been about a week since we had our wedding (ceremony, and reception) at Noor and we could not be happier with our entire experience. From the very beginning at our venue tour with Robert (owner), to the several days after our wedding with our amazing day of event coordinator/event manager, Amin. At the first visit with Robert, he was so easy going, upfront, and honest about the venue services and costs. We did not feel pressured to commit that day or add on every extra add-on or cost for our wedding. Later, for our first meeting with Noor we felt very impressed with Amin‚Äôs friendliness and professionalism. He answered all of questions at the meeting and responded to questions via email, phone, and text in a timely manner.

During the final meeting Amin was very cordial to our videographer, who joined us to get a lay of the land. This meeting, Amin guided us through our wedding timeline and answered our videographer‚Äôs questions; his attention to detail with certain needs was perfect. He even asked us a few things about our timeline that we had not even thought about.

This paragraph is a shout out to the main man with the plan behind the scenes. Amin absolutely slammed this thing out of the park, what more can you ask for out of this guy. Throughout the whole process he truly cared about our big day, and it was evident in all the detail. This would not have been possible without the support of an awesome, experienced, and caring day of coordinator. He even showed us the ballroom for approval of the setup before guests entered form the foyer after cocktail hour. That was unexpected to view our wedding reception prior and we were grateful for the considerate gesture. Also, poor Amin even gracefully handled answering demanding questions from one of our mothers before the wedding and dealt with a drunk headstrong godmother during the wedding.

We received so many compliments about the delicious duet plate; miso salmon and filet mignon. Relatives who never ate fish, ate the salmon and my mother who hardly eats red meat devoured her filet mignon. So, hats off to the chefs for the amazingly delicious meal, and thank you.
After the wedding, there was precious cargo left at Noor, and they were happy to safe guard our belongings until we were able to come pick them up 4 days later. This was so helpful because we did not have enough room the day of the wedding to pack everything into our car.
In conclusion, if you have not figured out from this novel-sized review, we would 10/10 recommend Noor to anyone looking for a brilliantly assembled, memorable, enjoyable wedding!

<Text>Planning a wedding can be a daunting task, but with the right team it can actually be a rather enjoyable experience. Robert and Maggie, the owners, of Noor took such great care of my husband and I that I felt like I was among family. They were extremely accommodating and were always super responsive.

After checking out a number of different venues in the Pasadena area, I fell in love with Noor's Sophia Ballroom (the Ella Ballroom is also beautiful but better suited for smaller events). Not only did it offer the elegant and modern style that I was looking for, but their prices were excellent, not to mention ALL INCLUSIVE! Yes, you heard that right! When you get your invoice you aren't going to find surprise fees or service charges, everything is already calculated directly into the price they show you from the beginning.

Now onto the important stuff. My husband and I opted for a full service OPEN BAR for the entire night! It was a great choice for us and our guests and Noor did an excellent job of keeping the drinks flowing and our guests happy. Now the second most important thing of the evening, the food. I love that we were able to request modifications during our tasting and that they were actually implemented for our wedding. Some of the highlights from our reception included the Chicken and Waffles, Coconut Shrimp, and Caprese Skewers (passed h'ordeuvres). We also served Boneless Ribeye, Grilled Salmon and Mushroom Raviolis as our entrees (the raviolis are a must try). If you do not want a plated dinner, they also have a myriad of other choices for you to choose from. As well as AV packages and anything else you might want to include for your wedding (like a photobooth).

The staff was always super friendly and helpful (even when our guests were getting kind of rowdy). I want to give a big thank you to their banquet manager Amin. He worked flawlessly with my other vendors and helped ensure that my special day went off without a hitch. I could not have asked for a better team and support group throughout this entire process. <Text>I am part of a nonprofit organization and we held our Mother's Day Luncheon in the Ella Ballroom.  Everything from the venue tour to the actual event went flawlessly.

To begin the process, Robert and I e-mailed back a forth a few times, just so I can have an idea of what exactly we could have for the budget we had for the event.  He sent me the proposal and I quickly realized that there's no other place where we could get as much as we were getting for the money we were paying...and I've done  A LOT of research.

A few of the ladies in the committee and I went for a site tour and immediately fell in love with the elegance, ambiance, and class of the space.  We liked that we were able to totally customize the space with our linen colors (napkins and table cloths) and even the LED ambient lighting color!

After booking the venue for our event, I bugged Robert several times with silly questions and he was always quick to get back to me.  He was very accommodating to our requests and last minute changes.

Fastforward to the day of the event......

When we walked in to start setting up nearly an hour before our event, the venue already looked so beautiful with the linens and the lighting.  The event managers were super helpful in assisting with our set up and answering all our questions.

FOOD: We chose two passed hors d'oeuvres to be served during our cocktail hour and we could not stop eating them.  They were truly exceptional.  We had chicken satay with a sesame peanut sauce (yum!) and wild mushroom roulades with oven-dried tomato aioli (DROOOOL!).  Our plated lunch consisted of a refreshing mixed green salad with a raspberry vinaigrette.  The dressing was sooooo yummy and I liked that they didn't dress the salad before they brought it out.  Everything was crisp and fresh.

Our second course was a duet of chicken breast with a wild mushroom champagne cream sauce (THE SAUCE!!) and grilled salmon with a citrus beurre blanc.  That salmon was some of the best salmon I've ever had.  The proteins were accompanied by herb roasted red potatoes and baby summer squash.  The dessert.  I'm dreaming about their cheesecake.  We opted to have several flavors of their cheesecake served family style.  SO GOOOOOOD!  The white chocolate salted caramel...oh my.  I can eat a GIANT slice of that deliciousness.  And the oreo....alksdjfl;aksdjf;laj.

Everyone raved about the food and several people said that this was our best event in our 11 years of hosting this Mother's Day Luncheon.  The AV equipment worked beautifully.  We had a singer, a DJ, a powerpoint presentation, and a speaker.  Everything in the ballroom was set-up to handle our needs perfectly.

Every last detail was perfect.  We had vendors attending our event so Noor set up tables with linens for them so everything would look uniform and beautiful.  Our theme was Breakfast at Tiffany's so Robert set up the movie to play in the background of our event.  Every lady that walked in was given a glass of champagne to start the event.  Everything was just SO elegant and beautiful.

The staff was extremely friendly.  The waiters, waitresses, and the bartenders helped make our event really awesome.  I personally thanked as many as I could before I left.

I highly recommend having an event here.  Everything was beautiful and the staff were amazing.  I can't wait to host another event at Noor!</Text>< Pics>

< review>
Below average in most catagories. All places start off at 4 stars and go from there. Customer service was mediocre at best. The decore was a decade or two old. <Review>This placed use to be a family favorite, but a few years ago they changed their menu--and ramped up their prices significantly.  Unfortunately, all that came with a steady decline in quality.  Sushi has never been their strong suit, but now even their main entrees have been suffering.  Their extra large portions have dwindled significantly along with the flavor, while retaining the high prices.  As a result, they've gone from one of my top favorites to one of my least favorites.  I much prefer making the drive up to Santa Cruz for Totoro or down to Watsonville for Miyuki if I'm in the mood for Japanese.  I miss the days of the Soquel location.<//Review><Pictures>None< /Pictures>< resp>

<rating>1</rating>< review>
I called Mike Diamond Plumbing after hearing their ads on the radio clearing drains for $99. I had a clogged kitchen drain that required snaking twice a year.    My first impression of their plumber was not good.  He used a hand power snake and poked a hole in the clog.  The water drained but it was still slow.  There was a heavy up-sale pitch.  The plumber wanted to re-pipe under my kitchen counter with brass at $700.  He gave me a quote for jet cleaning which was $700.  Their plumber dragged a steel wheeled jetter pump through my house over hardwood floors leaking water from my front door to the kitchen. The plumber said I would have to do both to get a guarantee.  When he reassembled the trap under the sink he left the pipes so the lateral pipes went uphill.  He left greasy, dirty handprints all over the pipes and around the cabinets.

I called another rooter service that was highly rated on Angie's List and had excellent results.  I would never call Mike Diamond again.</review>

For a very small location, I was surprised at just how delicious their food is. It's also pretty neat that they use shaved ice over traditional cubes or crushed. Their breakfast dishes are wholesome and comforting, their burgers and other lunch items are fantastic and savory, and their prices are perfect for any budget.

<user>105660939307047047367</user><user_name>jonathan bravo<//user_name><date>1422474363385< /date><rating>5< /rating>< Text>
Our AC started making a strange rumbling sound. I called JMS AC and Heating.  As promised, the technician showed up on time, professional, and polite.  I watched as he took apart the furnace and found the schematic label had fallen off and was sucked into the blower, which caused an imbalance. The technician then went about taking apart the blower and motor and cleaned them thoroughly.  Also inspected the coils, which showed they were pretty clean for a 9 year old machine.

Other than the diagnostic fee for coming out, there was no additional charge.  He did talk me into the service plan, which he believes (and I agree) is a good deal for an older AC unit.

On time, courteous, expert, and honest.  What more could you ask for? Will definitely be calling on JMS again in the future.< /Text>

<Rating>5< /Rating>< Review>
This review specifically goes out to Anthony in the Custom Framing department.

I was tasked by the firm I work for to get my diplomas framed. A coworker recommended Hobby Lobby, so naturally that was my first stop (went to the one across the way from this Michaels location). HORRIBLE experience at Hobby Lobby. I was observing the frame options at hobby lobby when the man working the framing department came out and sarcastically said, if you were ready you should have rung the bell. He asked what I was looking for, and I explained that I was wanting to get my diplomas framed. He was quick to dismiss any of my inquiries into custom framing and instead was pushing me to buy the 50% off ready made frames‚Äîum, if I wanted ready made frames, I would have started there... He seriously would not let it go, and kept insisting I look at the frames already on the floor and go with those. To say I was put off was an understatement. He asked if I had gotten my bachelor's degree. It wasn't until I told him I was looking to frame my Masters AND Law degree that he took me seriously and said, "oh SH**, okay, well if you really want you can do the custom framing..." It was a horrible experience and I decided to take my business elsewhere.

When I got to Michaels‚Äîa COMPLETE 180 from how I was treated in Hobby Lobby. There was no questioning of why I'd want to get custom framing over ready made frames or even of whether I could afford the service. Anthony was so ready and eager to help and exemplified incredible patience. He made great recommendations, walked me through the process and talked me through color options. I also observed how he was working with the customer just previous to us, and saw how he was incredibly professional and understanding to all of us who were waiting at the Framing department. It took me a good 20 minutes to make a decision on my framing options, but Anthony seemed to really understand what an important decision this was‚Äîthe diplomas are more than a piece of paper; they represent years of sacrifice and hard work.

I will definitely be recommending this Michaels and specifically the framing department to any of my friends who are looking to get their diplomas framed. Honestly, give Anthony a raise because he is most deserving.</Review>

<Date>1575743527102</Date><user_id>116243189429219957147</user_id>< Rating>
4</Rating>
<text>It's a nice enough Michaels if you like Michaels.  Michaels plays a lot of games with its pricing and coupons, which works for people who like that kind of thing, clipping coupons, paper or digital, going back multiple times, or getting in line mutiple times, to get the coupon discounts on more than one item. But it's a pain for someone who just wants to buy art or craft supplies for a good price. They inflate the original price, then put the item on "sale" so their coupons don't work on it. If they know their price, why not just charge it instead of all the pricing/coupon manipulation. To be a successful Michaels shoppper and get the best prices, you really have to master their sale/coupon/pricing scheme. Never shop at Michaels without going on line first to get the coupons of the day.  Good luck!< /text>< Pics>
